text: Nadja Schaus (born 8 November 1984 in Worms) is a German volleyball player. She played with the Germany women's national volleyball team at the 2009 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2010 FIVB World Grand Prix, 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship, 2011 FIVB World Grand Prix, and 2012 FIVB World Grand Prix. She played for Bayer 04 Leverkusen, Sigel Pallavolo Marsala, and USC Munster. == References == Category:1984 births Category:Living people Category:German volleyball players Category:People from Worms, Germany
